                <div id="input-container">
                    <form id="text_id" form method="post" action="/result" enctype="multipart/form-data">
                        <div id="text-area-container">
                            <textarea rows="20" cols="35" id="text-source" placeholder="Enter source!"
                                name="source"></textarea>
                            <textarea rows="20" cols="35" id="text-target" placeholder="Enter target!"
                                name="target"></textarea>
                        </div>
                        <p id="input-text"> or import files <i class="fa fa-laptop" aria-hidden="true"></i></p>
                        <div id="input-file-container">
                            <input type="file" id="myfile" class="custom-file-input" name="firstFile"
                                onchange="checkData()">
                            <input onchange="checkData()" type="file" id="myOtherfile" class="custom-file-input"
                                name="secondFile">
                        </div>
                        <button type="submit" id="check-btn" disabled><span onclick="checkTextAreaData()">Check
                                Similarity</span></button>

                    </form>

                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="web-check">

        <div id="web-title">
            <h1>Web-based plagiarism Check.</h1>
        </div>

        <div id="web-textarea-div">
            <form id="text" form method="post" action="/webResult">
                <h3>Check for plagiarism against numerous doucuments across the web.</h3>
                <textarea name="text" rows="15" cols="130" id="web-text" placeholder="Enter Text!"></textarea>
                <button type="submit" onclick="startLoader()" id="check-btn">Check Similarity</button>
            </form>
        </div>

    </section>

    <section id="FAQ">
        <div id="faq-containter">
            <h1 style="text-align: center;">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
            <div id="faq-div">
            </div>
            <div id="questions">

                <details>
                    <summary>
                        What does the standard check really do?
                        <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                        The standard-check feature enables you to check if your documents are unique. You can enter two
                        pieces of text or import two documents from your device and click the check similarity button to
                        view a similarity report.
                    </p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>
                        What does the web-check really do?
                        <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                        The web-check makes a google based search using every sentence in the text you have entered in
                        the text area. Upon clicking the check similarity button, you will receive a similarity report
                        listing all the plagiarised(in red) and unique sentences in the text provided. Clicking on each
                        plagiarised sentence will redirect you to the link where similar text was found.
                    </p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>
                        What's the difference between the standard check and the web check?
                        <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                        The standard-check carries a though plagiarism check between two pieces of text provided whereas
                        the web-check makes a google based plagiarism check for one piece of text.
                    </p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>
                        How does the standard check work?
                        <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                        This feature makes use of the Levenshtein Algorithm which calculates the Levenshtein Distance
                        between two text entries. The Levenshtein Distance is the minimum number of
                        single-character/string
                        edits required to change one word/document into the other. The Percentage similarity is thereby
                        derived from the result.
                    </p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>
                        How does the web check work?
                        <span class="icon"><i class="fas fa-chevron-down"></i></span>
                    </summary>
                    <p>
                        The web-check makes use of an npm library called serp which enables it to make a google based
                        search based on keywords which in this case will be the sentences entered in the text area.
                    </p>
                </details>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section>
